We only did this at the lowest times of the server population, but one night, upon clearing the king, we noticed a couple (pally and ranger if i recall) camping the priest, so we went past them.. and into the champ room. Champ was up ... so we set upon it, one at a time and by the time the room was cleared (champ being last on the list) we rested and healed up some. (down time minimal, she would barely get hit, i never evaded with just myself and her, and i have Mylorkar BP) ... <br>
Entering back into the King room to await the next round of spawn.. behold the pally that was in the priest stood there boldly claiming camp was his!...<br>
Now... fairs fair.. and not only did he try to enforce Play Nice , he couldn't my lady WAS after all gaining exp from the kills, but there was no way him and his partner could have broken and cleared the room without a horrendous train. So I kindly pointed these items out to him and asked him to leave. Upon which i was told of first to hit the spawn gave kill, anything else was considered KSíng. <br>
So we, my lady and myself, promptly dispatched the next two kills barely before he was able to react let alone get the first hit in... and to our disgust, he stood there defiant and started being a hotshot to his friend in priest about &quot; how his guild level 58 mage was enroute to outdamage a rogue &quot;. <br>
At which time, the third dog spawned, and i pulled an assasination. WHAM, 32000 damage, Solusek Kobold is dead faster than he barely finished a sentence...<br>
He left quietly after that, I never did see a 58 mage... but ten minutes later.. i got sent a tell from the pally, which went along of the lines of :<br>
&quot; all fighting aside... that WAS a real hit right? because i told my guild and no one will believe me &quot;..<br>
<br>
There is a kind of poetic justice after all in the EQ world huh  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
